<h1>Rails SVG Icons - cached and colorable</h1>
<p>
  This page renders <strong>10,000 icons</strong> (100x100 grid) using only <strong>4 SVG files</strong>.
  Open DevTools Network tab to verify only 4 icon requests are made.
</p>

<h2>How it works</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Each icon uses a helper: <code>&lt;%= icon :heart, color: :red, size: :lg %&gt;</code></li>
  <li>Renders as: <code>&lt;icon class="icon-red icon-lg" data-icon="heart"&gt;&lt;/icon&gt;</code></li>
  <li>CSS <code>mask-image</code> uses the SVG as a stencil</li>
  <li><code>background-color</code> provides the visible color</li>
  <li>SVGs are cached - 10,000 icons = 4 HTTP requests total</li>
</ul>

<h2>10,000 Icons Grid</h2>
<div class="icon-grid">
  <% icons = %i[heart lock star bell] %>
  <% colors = %i[red blue green purple amber] %>
  <% sizes = %i[sm md lg] %>
  <% 10_000.times do %>
    <%= icon icons.sample, color: colors.sample, size: sizes.sample %>
  <% end %>
</div>
